# Reference wiring summary; APPLY_RENDER_INTERPOLATION.mjs is authoritative.

src/main.js
- import RenderPoseInterpolator and renderInterpolationAlpha
- instantiate one interpolator beside FlightModel
- capture the completed pose after every flight.step()
- compute alpha = accumulator / CONFIG.physics.fixedStep
- sample one sharedRenderPose per display frame
- pass sharedRenderPose to CameraRig.update and AircraftVisualSystem.update
- leave collision/effects/world/HUD on raw flight
- reset interpolation after spawn, respawn/reset, recovery teleport,
  floating-origin shift, dropped physics time, visibility change and pageshow

src/camera.js
- reset(renderPose) and update(dt, renderPose, ...)
- derive position/attitude/FOV/third-person target from renderPose
- keep viewYaw current; apply head look and camera shake after the base pose

src/aircraftVisuals.js
- update(dt, renderPose, cameraMode)
- copy external root position/quaternion from renderPose
- retain child propeller rotation and instruments
- remove cockpitRoot speed sine offsets
